{"lemma":"بَقَراتٌ","slug":"بَقَراتٌ","root":"ب.ق.ر","root_slug":"ب-ق-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ق-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَقَر","root":"بقر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2985","n2988"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cattle, oxen","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"قَالُوا ٱدْعُ لَنَا رَبَّكَ يُبَيِّنْ لَنَا مَا هِيَ إِنَّ ٱلْبَقَرَ تَشَابَهَ عَلَيْنَا وَإِنَّا إِنْ شَاءَ ٱللَّٰهُ لَمُهْتَدُونَ","english":"\"Call out to your Lord,\" they said, \"so that he may clear it up for us: all cattle are alike to us, but we, God willing, can be led forward.\""},{"text":"Al-Buhturi\nعليّ نحت القوافي من مقَاَطِعِها / وما علي إذا لم تفهم البقرُ","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to split, to rip, to rive"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dig up, to gut"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew בָּקָר (bāqār)."},"ipa":["/ba.qar/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2985","headword_ar":"بَقَرَ","root":"bqr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, A, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [but this seems to be a mistake,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqorN","text_ar":"بَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He slit; ripped; split; cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divided, lengthwise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, &c.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He slit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ripped open,"},{"kind":"text","text":"an animal's belly. (A, Mgh.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AuboqurohaA Eano janiynihaA","text_ar":"اُبْقُرْهَا عَنْ جَنِينِهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rip thou open her"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a camel's]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belly so as to disclose her fœtus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiyrN","text_ar":"بَقِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He opened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laid open."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He widened; made wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ample."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He opened, and widened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a house, or tent. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He opened and revealed"},{"kind":"text","text":"to a person a story. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqara AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"بَقَرَ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hudohud","text_ar":"هُدْهُد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or hoopoe],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It looked for the place of water and saw it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it clave the ground and discovered water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] occurring in a trad. respecting the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hdhd","text_ar":"هدهد"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Solomon [mentioned in the Kur ch. xxvii.] (T.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqara fiY baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"بَقَرَ فِى بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He knew the state, condition, case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair, of the sons of such a one, and examined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inspected, them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqara Eani AlEuluwmi","text_ar":"بَقَرَ عَنِ العُلُومِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inquired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"searched"},{"kind":"page_break","n":234},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the utmost, after sciences."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqara AlEiloma","text_ar":"بَقَرَ العِلْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 5.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqira","text_ar":"بَقِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a dog)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became confounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and stupified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with joy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at seeing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqar","text_ar":"بَقَر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqar AlwaHo$","text_ar":"بَقَر الوَحْش"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild oxen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild bulls"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cows"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazila","text_ar":"غَزِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ he sported, ” or “ played, ” “ at seeing a gazelle, ” or “ a young gazelle; ” as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoqara","text_ar":"بَيْقَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": or the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he feared, so that he was astonished, amazed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stupified, at seeing many"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqar","text_ar":"بَقَر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHiza","text_ar":"بَحِزَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and ↓ the latter signifies also [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became confounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he doubted respecting a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  Also, aor. as above, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarN","text_ar":"بَقَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqorN","text_ar":"بَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) but Az says, El-Mundhiree has informed me that A Heyth disallowed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqorN","text_ar":"بَقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", saying that it is accord. to analogy"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarN","text_ar":"بَقَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as the verb is intrans.; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became tired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fatigued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he could hardly see;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became weary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jaded;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoqara","text_ar":"بَيْقَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K. *)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n2988","headword_ar":"بَقَرٌ","root":"bqr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a gen. n., (S, Msb,) a word of well-known meaning, (S, Msb, K,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bovine genus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ox,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bull,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oxen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cows; neat; black cattle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"domestic"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [but the wild have also distinctive appellations, as will be seen below:] n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarapN","text_ar":"بَقَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, [but in the K it is said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarN","text_ar":"بَقَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarapN","text_ar":"بَقَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) which is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"being added only to restrict it to unity: (S, Msb:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarN","text_ar":"بَقَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboqurN","text_ar":"اَبْقُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.]; (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboqaArN","text_ar":"اَبْقَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herds of oxen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abl","text_ar":"ابل"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarapN","text_ar":"بَقَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaraAtN","text_ar":"بَقَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buqurN","text_ar":"بُقُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buq~aArN","text_ar":"بُقَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaAqiru","text_ar":"بَوَاقِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uboquwrN","text_ar":"اُبْقُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) [or rather this last is a quasi-pl. n.;] and the following [also] are quasi-pl. ns., namely, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoquwrN","text_ar":"بَيْقُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarN","text_ar":"بَقَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiyrN","text_ar":"بَقِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or this signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herd, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqar","text_ar":"بَقَر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqirN","text_ar":"بَاقِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or this signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herd, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqar","text_ar":"بَقَر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with their pastors,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAquwrN","text_ar":"بَاقُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAquwrapN","text_ar":"بَاقُورَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or this last is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarapN","text_ar":"بَقَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the dial. of the people of El-Yemen: (S:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAquwrN","text_ar":"بَاقُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaboquwrN","text_ar":"يَبْقُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uboquwrN","text_ar":"اُبْقُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are all syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarN","text_ar":"بَقَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so, accord. to Ktr, is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAquwrapN","text_ar":"بَاقُورَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaru AlwaHo$i","text_ar":"بَقَرُ الوَحْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaqaru AlwaHo$iY~u","text_ar":"البَقَرُ الوَحْشِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wild ox,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bull,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild oxen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"collectively: n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarapu AlwaHo$i","text_ar":"بَقَرَةُ الوَحْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaqarapu AlwaHo$iy~apu","text_ar":"البَقَرَةُ الوَحْشِيَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; masc. and fem.: in Egypt, these appellations are applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"antilope defassa"},{"kind":"text","text":"of modern zoologists: so says Sir Gardner Wilkinson; and to this, I believe, they generally apply in the poems &c. of the early Arabs: it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of bovine antelope:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in Barbary, it seems that the animal thus called is another species of bovine antelope, or perhaps a variety of the former; it is said to be what is termed by Pallas"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"antilope bubalis;"},{"kind":"text","text":"by others,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alcephalus bubalis,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acronotus bubalis;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is said to come occasionally to the Nile: but the Arabic appellations given above are employed with much laxity: thus we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqaru AlwaHo$i","text_ar":"بَقَرُ الوَحْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"explained as meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of animal of which there are four different species: the first called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mihiA","text_ar":"مِهِا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahFA","text_ar":"مَهًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", a coll. gen. n. of which the n. un. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahaApN","text_ar":"مَهَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the second,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ayl","text_ar":"ايل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~alN","text_ar":"اـِيَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the third"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yHmwr","text_ar":"يحمور"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHomuwrN","text_ar":"يَحْمُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yAmwr","text_ar":"يامور"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA^omuwrN","text_ar":"يَاْمُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fourth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vyvl","text_ar":"ثيثل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vayotalN","text_ar":"ثَيْتَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wEl","text_ar":"وعل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEolN","text_ar":"وَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Ed-Demeeree, cited by De Sacy, erroneously written by him “ Domaïri, ” in his Chrest. Ar. sec. ed. ii. 435 et seq.:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called in Persian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kwzn","text_ar":"كوزن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Gawazono","text_ar":"گَوَزْنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~alN","text_ar":"اـِيَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Awl","text_ar":"اول"},{"kind":"text","text":")];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it has a great horn, with branches; an additional branch growing upon its horn every year; and its horn is solid, thus differing from the horns of other animals, for their horns are hollow: when it hears singing, and the sounds of musical instruments, it listens thereto, and then it takes no care to guard itself from the arrows, by reason of its intense delight therein: when it raises its ear, it hears sounds; and when it relaxes it, it hears not anything."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw: also cited by De Sacy, ubi suprà.) The Arabs regard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqar","text_ar":"بَقَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bqr AlwH$","text_ar":"بقر الوحش"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as ominous of evil, because of the sharpness of their horns. (Ham p. 285.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"milo'u masoki Albaqarapi","text_ar":"مِلْءُ مَسْكِ البَقَرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The quantity that fills the hide of the bull,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large quantity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~ibaA='a EalaY Albaqari","text_ar":"الظِّبَا=ءَ عَلَى البَقَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~ibaA='u","text_ar":"الظِّبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkiraAba EalaY Albaqari","text_ar":"الكِرَابَ عَلَى البَقَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkiraAbu","text_ar":"الكِرَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkilaAba","text_ar":"الكِلَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkilaAbu","text_ar":"الكِلَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] are provs. of the Arabs. (TA.) [See arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zby","text_ar":"ظبي"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"krb","text_ar":"كرب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"klb","text_ar":"كلب"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayonu Albaqari","text_ar":"عَيْنُ البَقَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The buphthalmum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ox-eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahaArN","text_ar":"بَهَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bhr","text_ar":"بهر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euyuwnu Albaqari","text_ar":"عُيُونُ البَقَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of grape, black, large, round, and not very sweet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) In Palestine, applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ij~aAS","text_ar":"اـِجَّاص"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plum"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarN","text_ar":"بَقَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A family,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"household; those who dwell with a man, and whose maintenance is incumbent on him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA'a fulaAnN yajur~u baqarahu","text_ar":"جَاءَ فُلَانٌ يَجُرُّ بَقَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came dragging along his family,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"household."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY fulaAnK baqarapN mino EiyaAlK","text_ar":"عَلَى فُلَانٍ بَقَرَةٌ مِنْ عِيَالٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaAlK","text_ar":"وَمَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Upon such a one is dependent a troop,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large number, of his family, and of camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * TA;) and in like manner you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kari$N mino EiyaAlK","text_ar":"كَرِشٌ مِنْ عِيَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN fiY baqarK mina Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ فِى بَقَرٍ مِنَ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is among a large company of men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","M","As","T","Lth"]}]}}